## Known Findings (do not duplicate)

- F-001: Anyone can front-run initialization and permanently seize an uninitialized pool (Critical, high)
- F-002: Collateral withdrawals pass health checks because redemption validates before the asset transfer leaves the pool (Critical, high)
- F-003: New LPs can steal previously accrued borrower interest because `lend()` mints shares against stale debt (High, high)
- F-004: Liquidation uses `100 - lb` instead of the borrow limit, creating a large undercollateralized but non-liquidatable zone (High, high)


